source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/pork-satay-burgers-with-paprika-sweet-potato-wedges-574eeaa3fd2cb930678b4567
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Pre-heat your oven to 220 degrees. Chop the @sweet potato{2} into wedges roughly the
width and length of your index finger. Put them on a #baking tray{}, drizzle over
@oil{2%tbsp}, sprinkle over half the @smoked paprika{1/2}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and a
grind of @ground black pepper{1%grind}. Make sure everything is evenly coated and
put in your oven to cook for ~{25%minutes}.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%stalks}(roughly chopped, stalks and leaves!) and
zest the @lime{2} with a #grater{}. Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{3}. Put the
@British pork mince{600%g} in a #bowl{} and add three quarters of your
coriander along with your lime zest, chopped peanuts, the other half of your
smoked paprika, half the @soy sauce{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of
ground black pepper.

> Don't make the burgers too thick, they will change shape as the proteins tighten
> up while they are being cooked.

Combine everything together with your hands and shape into four burgers about 2cm
thick.

Remove the tough rooty bit off the @baby gem lettuce{2}(washed and roughly chopped)
and cut into roughly 2cm slices. Peel, grate the @carrot{2} and mix it with the
lettuce. Mix @olive oil{2%tbsp} with the juice from one half of one of the limes
and a pinch of salt and pepper, whisk together with a #fork{}. Put most of your
lettuce and carrot into a bowl (reserve a little to put on the burgers!) and throw
in your limey dressing. Toss the salad.

> If you're not that keen on lime, use a bit less than specified!

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add @oil{2%tbsp}. Add your burgers and cook
for ~{5%minutes} on each side before adding them to a baking tray. Put the burgers
in your oven to carry on cooking for ~{5%minutes} while you make the sauce.

Put the @peanut butter{3%tbsp} in a bowl and add the juice from the other lime.
Add @water{2%tbsp}, the rest of the @soy sauce{2%tsp} and the rest of the coriander
and mix everything together with a fork.

> Only add as much lime as you like to taste.

Turn your grill to high and cut the @brioche bun{4} in half. Put your buns under the
#grill{} for ~{1-2%minutes} on each side to toast them.

> Keep an eye on the buns, you don't want them to burn!

When everything is ready, spread your satay sauce on the bottom half of your buns,
pop your burgers on top, top with some lettuce carrot mixture and pop the bun top
on. Serve with a side of sweet potato wedges and salad! YUM!